{"key":"post-10401055","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10401055</id>\n<content>The so-called frosting layer is bunk.&amp;nbsp; Exposed grains on the surface leave an opening for contamination.&amp;nbsp; This has been proved for many years, and the original poster who came up with the idea of 'frosting' promptly rejected it after a few tries.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Mix gently or layer, but make sure you leave a layer of bulk substrate on the surface, never exposed grains.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10401067</next>\n<prev>10401012</prev>\n<first>10400658</first>\n<last>10407119</last>\n<when>1243352108</when>\n<utime>05/26/09 06:35 PM</utime>\n</post>"}